WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:22.080
The dog, inu, ichi ninsho, tansu no daimeishi, I, my, me, mine, sono yore, I am a dog, I have a master, my master is very kind to me, he takes me everywhere he goes, mine is the best of masters,

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:43.439
二人称、単数の代名詞、 You, your, you, yours, sono yore, You are a dog, you have a master, your master is very kind to you, he takes you everywhere he goes, yours is the best of masters,

00:00:43.439 --> 00:01:05.599
三人称、単数、男性の代名詞、 He, his, him, his, sono yore, He is a dog, he has a master, his master is very kind to him, he takes him everywhere he goes, his is the best of masters,

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:29.760
同じく、三人称、単数、女性の代名詞、 She, her, her, hers, sono yore, She is a dog, she has a master, her master is very kind to her, he takes her everywhere he goes, hers is the best of masters,

00:01:29.919 --> 00:01:54.400
同じく、三人称、単数、中性の代名詞、 It, its, its, its, sono yore, It is a dog, it has a master, its master is very kind to it, he takes it everywhere he goes, its is the best of masters,

00:01:55.040 --> 00:02:16.320
一人称、複数の代名詞、 We, our, us, ours, sono yore, We are dogs, we have a master, our master is very kind to us, he takes us everywhere he goes, ours is the best of masters,

00:02:16.399 --> 00:02:27.839
二人称、複数の代名詞は、 You, your, you, yours, de, 単数の時と同じ形です。

00:02:27.839 --> 00:02:49.600
三人称、複数の代名詞、 They, their, them, theirs, sono yore, They are dogs, they have a master, their master is kind to them, he takes them everywhere he goes, theirs is the best of masters,

00:02:49.759 --> 00:03:16.160
人称代名詞、 Personal pronouns, 日本語では、私、あなた、あなた方、というような言葉を使う場合、その言葉の語尾に、がの、にを、それぞれ必要に応じて、別に他から言い添えて、その言葉の関係を示しますが、

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:29.440
英語の代名詞では、がの、にをの区別が、言葉そのものの中に、はじめから含められて、取り外しのできないことになっております。

